eNCA's Thubelihle Vilane joins us from the scene of the accident near Pietermaritzburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Thirteen people have died in a crash involving a petrol tanker and a minibus near Pietermaritzburg. READ: Ten killed, several injured in Golden Highway collision Six people have sustained injuries, 2 of them critical. The cause of the accident is not yet known, and authorities have closed off the road. An investigation is underway.